ed polar cap, and that the\nconversion of spin-down power to gamma-ray luminosity in B0355+54 must be low.\nThe new proper motion for B1929+10 also implies that its progenitor is unlikely\nto have been the binary companion of the runaway O-star zeta-Ophiuchi.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Dec 2003 21:04:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
